body:
Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
```systemverilog
interface iface #(parameter DWIDTH = 32)();
  localparam TOTAL_PACKED_WIDTH = DWIDTH + 1;
  modport Tx(output sop, data, import unpack);
  logic sop;
  logic [DWIDTH - 1:0]  data = '0;

  task static unpack(input logic [TOTAL_PACKED_WIDTH-1:0] packed_in, input logic sop_i);
    logic sop_nc;
    {data, sop_nc} <= packed_in;
    sop <= sop_i;
  endtask
endinterface

module t;
iface ifc();
endmodule
```
output:
```
%Error: Internal Error: foo.sv:9:23: ../V3Scope.cpp:72: Can't locate varref scope
                                   : ... note: In instance 't.ifc'
    9 |     {data, sop_nc} <= packed_in;
      |                       ^~~~~~~~~
```
What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
`verilator --binary -j 0 -Wall foo.sv`

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
`Verilator 5.028 2024-08-21 rev conda-forge build 0`. No.
What OS and distribution are you using?
Linux x86
May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
Sure
